<p>This works fine.</p>  <pre><code> FOR /f "delims=" %%G in ('TagRead.exe %%L Genre') DO ( echo %GG ) </code></pre>  <p>But when I add a <code>sed</code> command to the ('...') it fails</p>  <pre><code> FOR /f "delims=" %%G in (  'TagRead.exe %%L Genre ^| sed -E ''/Curtain^|Exit^|Spacer/^^!s~.*~Dance~'' '  ) DO ( echo %%G) </code></pre>  <p>output:</p>  <pre><code> sed: newline or end of file found in pattern </code></pre>  <p>How do I get the sed command and its quotes to be accepted in the (...) quotes?</p>